column5: leaving for lake tobin on sep 11 any segestions for the walleye and pike bite any help would great thanks in advance terry

Hey how did your trip end up? Are you the same triton from sloughshark.net? We went and fished yesterday, the fishing was slow but size was definetly there. We were able to get 3 over 10 pounds, fished from 8-4. Also a couple little ones, it is slow going but they are big. Any other reports?
The crank bite is starting to kick in a bit at night, number of good fish were caught out by the nest last night, the weather was amazing too!!
